---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="DMCA and Copyright - SkillStart Jobs" description="Report copyright issues.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="/">Home</a> / DMCA and Copyright</div>
      <h1>DMCA and Copyright</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="content-card">
        <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> April 19, 2026</p>
        <p>SkillStart Jobs respects the intellectual property rights of others and expects users, contributors, and third parties to do the same.</p>
        <p>This Digital Millennium Copyright Act (&ldquo;DMCA&rdquo;) Policy explains how copyright infringement claims may be submitted regarding content available on skillstartjobs.online.</p>
        <p>If you believe that material on our website infringes your copyright, please follow the procedure below.</p>

        <h2>1. Copyright Respect</h2>
        <p>We aim to publish original, properly sourced, or lawfully used content. However, if you believe copyrighted material has been used without authorization, please notify us so we can review the matter promptly.</p>

        <h2>2. Filing a Copyright Complaint</h2>
        <p>If you are a copyright owner or authorized representative, please send a written notice including the following:</p>
        <p><strong>Required Information</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your full name and contact information</li>
          <li>Your email address</li>
          <li>A description of the copyrighted work claimed to be infringed</li>
          <li>The exact URL(s) on skillstartjobs.online where the allegedly infringing content appears</li>
          <li>A statement that you have a good faith belief the disputed use is not authorized by the copyright owner, agent, or law</li>
          <li>A statement that the information in your notice is accurate</li>
          <li>A statement made under penalty of perjury that you are the copyright owner or authorized to act on behalf of the owner</li>
          <li>Your physical or electronic signature</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Where to Send Notices</h2>
        <p>Please submit DMCA notices through our <a href="/contact/">Contact Page</a> on skillstartjobs.online or via the official email address listed there.</p>
        <p>Use the subject line:</p>
        <p><strong>DMCA Takedown Request</strong></p>

        <h2>4. Review Process</h2>
        <p>After receiving a valid complaint, we may:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Review the reported content</li>
          <li>Request additional information</li>
          <li>Temporarily remove or restrict access to content</li>
          <li>Permanently remove infringing material where appropriate</li>
          <li>Notify the relevant contributor or party if applicable</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We aim to respond within a reasonable timeframe.</p>

        <h2>5. Counter Notification</h2>
        <p>If you believe content was removed by mistake or misidentification, you may submit a counter-notification including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your full name and contact details</li>
          <li>Identification of removed content and its previous location</li>
          <li>A statement under penalty of perjury that you believe removal was a mistake or misidentification</li>
          <li>Consent to jurisdiction where legally required</li>
          <li>Your physical or electronic signature</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We may review and act according to applicable law.</p>

        <h2>6. Repeat Infringers</h2>
        <p>SkillStart Jobs reserves the right to restrict or block access from users, contributors, or sources repeatedly involved in copyright infringement.</p>

        <h2>7. Good Faith Requirement</h2>
        <p>False, misleading, abusive, or fraudulent copyright complaints may create legal consequences under applicable laws.</p>
        <p>Please submit notices only when you have a genuine legal basis.</p>

        <h2>8. Third-Party Content & External Links</h2>
        <p>Our website may reference or link to third-party job listings, employer websites, or external resources.</p>
        <p>We do not control third-party websites and are not responsible for copyright issues occurring on external platforms.</p>
        <p>Complaints regarding third-party websites should be directed to the respective website owner.</p>

        <h2>9. No Legal Advice</h2>
        <p>This DMCA Policy is provided for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal advice.</p>
        <p>If you need legal guidance, please consult a qualified attorney.</p>

        <h2>10. Policy Updates</h2>
        <p>We may update this DMCA Policy at any time without prior notice. Updated versions will be posted on this page with the revised date.</p>

        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>For copyright-related concerns, please use the <a href="/contact/">Contact Page</a> on skillstartjobs.online and mention:</p>
        <p><strong>DMCA Request</strong></p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>


